02:21.108 --> 02:24.109
So, have you been
thinking about names?

02:24.111 --> 02:26.111
If you have a boy,
what're you gonna name him?

02:27.081 --> 02:28.714
And you better be having a boy.

02:28.716 --> 02:30.149
Yeah, yeah.

02:30.151 --> 02:32.851
Uh, yeah, one of those old
fashioned names like, uh, Levi,

02:32.853 --> 02:35.087
or like Homer or something.

02:35.589 --> 02:38.090
Homer? Over my dead body.

02:57.411 --> 02:58.744
Pardon the intrusion, ma'am.

02:58.746 --> 03:00.612
My name is Aksel Brandr.

03:00.614 --> 03:02.314
I wish to speak
with your husband.

03:02.716 --> 03:04.183
Is he available?

03:04.185 --> 03:08.353
Jacob. He's, he's out fishing,
but he'll be back any minute.

03:08.355 --> 03:09.655
Anything I could do for you?

03:09.657 --> 03:12.057
It's best
that I speak directly with him.

03:12.059 --> 03:14.293
Involves an important
business proposition.

03:15.262 --> 03:17.963
Well, you're welcome
to wait inside.

03:17.965 --> 03:19.298
Much obliged.

03:20.434 --> 03:21.433
Just have a seat.

03:23.671 --> 03:26.638
It shouldn't be
much longer.

03:26.640 --> 03:28.006
I'll go look for him.

03:50.564 --> 03:52.531
Jacob!

03:52.533 --> 03:54.399
There's a young man here
to see you.

03:54.735 --> 03:55.867
Who?

03:55.869 --> 03:57.569
Name is Aksel.

03:57.571 --> 04:00.439
Says he wants to talk to you
about a business proposition.

04:21.929 --> 04:23.662
Mr. Richardson.

04:23.664 --> 04:25.530
It's a pleasure
to meet you, sir.

04:25.532 --> 04:27.432
My name is Aksel Brandr.

04:27.434 --> 04:29.935
I'm here on behalf
of my father, Henrik Brandr.

04:30.671 --> 04:33.005
Yes... Nice to meet you.

04:34.375 --> 04:35.507
Askel...

04:36.944 --> 04:38.377
What can I do for you?

04:38.379 --> 04:39.945
Well, I know
you're a busy man, sir.

04:39.947 --> 04:41.546
So I'll get right to it.

04:41.548 --> 04:44.983
My father is very interested
in purchasing your land.

04:44.985 --> 04:48.053
In fact, he's willing to pay
a handsome amount for it.

04:48.055 --> 04:49.655
You name the price.

04:52.059 --> 04:53.692
Well, I appreciate the offer.

04:53.694 --> 04:55.327
I really do, but...

04:57.431 --> 04:59.097
this land ain't for sale...

04:59.867 --> 05:02.100
for any price.

05:02.102 --> 05:05.070
There must be some amount
that could change your mind.

05:05.072 --> 05:07.639
Think of the future your family
could have with this money.

05:08.942 --> 05:11.009
You listen to me, young man.

05:12.613 --> 05:15.414
This is my family's house.

05:16.550 --> 05:20.952
I designed it. I helped build it
with my bare hands.

05:22.623 --> 05:29.027
This land belongs to my family,
Not to your father

05:29.029 --> 05:30.562
or anybody else,
for that matter.

05:34.635 --> 05:39.438
Just exactly, what the hell does
he want with my land, anyway?

05:39.940 --> 05:41.239
He has his reasons.

05:41.775 --> 05:43.008
Is that right?

05:50.351 --> 05:51.450
I'm sorry...

05:53.253 --> 05:55.620
I'm gonna have to ask you
to leave.

05:58.525 --> 06:00.225
Well, Mr. Richardson,

06:00.227 --> 06:03.795
I understand that this is
a difficult decision to make.

06:03.797 --> 06:07.432
We'll give you some time to
consider the financial benefits.

06:08.669 --> 06:10.569
In the meantime,

06:10.571 --> 06:13.271
please give my father's regards
to your family.

06:14.875 --> 06:16.208
Here's my card.

06:35.129 --> 06:36.094
Hey.

06:36.096 --> 06:37.863
Hey, hey, how was your day?

06:37.865 --> 06:39.331
Not too bad.

06:39.333 --> 06:42.834
Dad and I, uh,
went fishing, and...

06:42.836 --> 06:44.236
Now we were just hanging out

06:44.238 --> 06:47.339
and they're having drinks,
not me.

06:47.341 --> 06:48.740
But...

06:48.742 --> 06:50.075
<i>Anyway, how are you?</i>

06:50.077 --> 06:52.244
I had to put a mastiff to sleep,
so that was a bummer.

06:52.246 --> 06:55.013
But, uh,
how's your little embryo doing?

06:55.015 --> 06:56.748
Doing just fine.

06:56.750 --> 07:00.552
Hey, Dr. Labelle said it will
probably start kicking in 12 weeks.

07:00.554 --> 07:03.622
Yeah, that sounds about right.
Usually takes about 20 weeks.

07:05.659 --> 07:07.292
God, I wish I could be there
with you right now.

07:08.362 --> 07:09.361
I miss you.

07:09.696 --> 07:11.029
I miss you, too.

07:11.765 --> 07:13.665
You need to get
your ass up here.

07:13.667 --> 07:15.167
I know.

07:15.169 --> 07:18.503
Just three more days, and I will zip
right up there, seven hours non-stop.

07:18.505 --> 07:21.006
And I will make
the sweetest love to you ever.

07:21.008 --> 07:23.108
I can't wait.

07:24.211 --> 07:26.144
God, I swear, it's like
pregnancy makes me

07:26.146 --> 07:28.380
<i>extra horny or something,
honey, I don't know.</i>

07:28.382 --> 07:30.248
Aw, Rebecca,
you are torturing me.

07:30.250 --> 07:31.716
Yeah, you've no idea.

07:35.556 --> 07:36.855
You stop.

07:36.857 --> 07:38.290
Whoa, um...

07:38.826 --> 07:40.559
Hey, I gotta go.

07:40.561 --> 07:43.662
But, I'll call you
later after dinner, okay?

07:44.398 --> 07:45.297
Okay.

07:45.299 --> 07:47.032
Tell them I said, "Howdy."

07:47.034 --> 07:49.167
I will. I love you.

07:49.169 --> 07:50.368
I love you too.

07:50.804 --> 07:51.803
All right, bye.

07:52.439 --> 07:53.405
<i>Bye.</i>

08:01.882 --> 08:03.081
Can I help you?

08:20.100 --> 08:21.733
<i> Hey,</i>
<i>you've reached Rebecca.</i>

08:21.735 --> 08:23.902
<i>Leave me a message and I'll get
back to you as soon as I can.</i>

08:25.339 --> 08:27.973
Hey, honey, I'm about to go
paddle boarding, I've got to go.

08:27.975 --> 08:29.508
Shift doesn't start
for a couple hours.

08:29.510 --> 08:35.080
So, uh, it's a beautiful day
here in Malibu, as always.

08:35.082 --> 08:38.383
Anyway, you're probably still
asleep, so I'll talk to you later.

08:38.719 --> 08:39.851
Love you. Bye.

10:49.182 --> 10:50.682
<i>Hi, this is Mark Neville,</i>

10:50.684 --> 10:52.851
<i>please leave a message
and I'll get back to you.</i>

10:54.388 --> 10:55.587
It's voicemail again.

10:58.325 --> 11:00.392
How many times
have you tried calling him?

11:03.530 --> 11:05.897
This is not like him.
I don't know.

11:20.714 --> 11:23.682
Good morning, Jacob.
I need to have a word with Rebecca.

11:23.684 --> 11:24.983
- Is she available?
- Yeah.

11:28.088 --> 11:29.721
What do you need
to talk to her for?

11:31.258 --> 11:32.290
Jacob, I...

11:32.292 --> 11:33.725
I hate to tell you this.

11:33.727 --> 11:36.227
Medical examiners
working on identifying a body

11:36.229 --> 11:37.829
that washed up on the beach
in Malibu.

11:40.000 --> 11:43.435
Given the circumstances,
Rebecca reported last night...

11:43.437 --> 11:45.437
We believe
it may be your son-in-law.

11:52.279 --> 11:53.478
Dad, what's wrong?

11:56.083 --> 11:57.382
Rebecca, they, uh...

11:58.919 --> 12:01.720
They found a body in Malibu.

12:01.722 --> 12:04.689
They need us to go down there and help
'em make a positive identification,

12:04.691 --> 12:07.525
- but it's possible it's not Mark.
- Oh, no.

12:07.527 --> 12:09.427
I hope to God it's not him.

12:09.429 --> 12:11.062
Wh... What happened to him?

12:11.064 --> 12:14.432
Some sort of freak accident it
was, they say, it was a shark bite,

12:14.434 --> 12:16.634
but it might not be Mark.

12:17.437 --> 12:18.837
I'll keep him in my prayers.

12:19.439 --> 12:20.805
Let's hope for the best.

12:23.276 --> 12:24.609
Come on.

12:37.057 --> 12:41.392
Rebecca, honey, you need anything?
Maybe some tea?

12:43.964 --> 12:48.366
Okay, well...
I'll go make some just in case.

13:19.266 --> 13:21.166
Jacob!

13:22.102 --> 13:23.268
What the hell happened?

13:23.270 --> 13:24.736
There was somebody out there.

13:31.511 --> 13:33.745
Lock this door
and call the Sheriff.

13:57.204 --> 13:58.203
What the hell?

14:19.559 --> 14:21.593
Whoever did this is sick.

14:22.863 --> 14:24.195
Hey, John.

14:24.197 --> 14:28.099
Listen, I'm sorry to get you out on
such a God awful night like this.

14:28.101 --> 14:31.102
That's okay. Your family's been
through enough this week.

14:31.104 --> 14:35.773
If anybody's been trespassing on your
property, I'm gonna find out who it is.

14:35.775 --> 14:39.177
I got to tell you, I've never
seen anything like this before.

14:40.080 --> 14:41.579
Why would someone come
all the way out here

14:41.581 --> 14:43.915
to put ashes and dead birds
on your porch?

14:46.219 --> 14:50.388
There was a strange kid that
showed up back, Aksel Brandr.

14:50.390 --> 14:52.190
His father wanted
to buy my property,

14:52.192 --> 14:54.893
but they wouldn't tell me why.

14:54.895 --> 14:58.563
He was really vague about it,
so I refused them.

14:58.565 --> 15:00.565
Of course,
I'm not selling this place.

15:00.567 --> 15:02.901
Did he give anything?
Any information?

15:07.407 --> 15:10.041
He gave me his card.
Aksel Brandr.

15:11.344 --> 15:12.343
Everything's clear. sir.

15:12.345 --> 15:14.779
Okay, good. Thank you.

15:14.781 --> 15:16.915
All right, listen, I'll have
forensics check for any evidence.

15:16.917 --> 15:19.117
If we find anything,
we'll let you know.

15:19.119 --> 15:22.687
In the meantime,
you see anybody trespassing...

15:23.123 --> 15:24.122
give me a call.

15:26.760 --> 15:27.892
I will.

15:29.095 --> 15:30.628
All right. You take care.

15:32.532 --> 15:33.898
Thanks, John.

15:35.835 --> 15:36.834
Thanks, Tommy.

16:37.564 --> 16:41.199
Oh, oh, oh, God.

16:44.137 --> 16:45.169
Oh, God.

16:47.140 --> 16:48.106
Mom!

16:48.108 --> 16:49.273
Rebecca.

16:49.275 --> 16:50.608
What's wrong?

16:50.610 --> 16:52.176
Oh, my God.

16:52.178 --> 16:54.645
- Come on, honey.
- We need to get her to the hospital.

17:41.928 --> 17:43.895
You know,
I don't understand it.

17:47.200 --> 17:49.934
First Mark... Baby.

17:49.936 --> 17:54.238
It's like, uh,
we're being picked off by God himself.

17:55.708 --> 17:57.875
Something evil
has happened, Jacob.

17:59.112 --> 18:01.312
I think someone put a curse
on us last night,

18:01.314 --> 18:03.915
and that's why they left those
terrible things on our porch.

18:03.917 --> 18:06.184
I don't believe
in curses, Elena.

18:07.454 --> 18:08.786
That's nonsense.

18:08.788 --> 18:10.755
Besides, who the hell
would do something like that?

18:12.392 --> 18:15.426
There was something strange
about that young man, Aksel.

18:23.770 --> 18:26.104
- Shit.
- Oh, Rebecca.

18:29.309 --> 18:31.042
<i>Hey, you've reached Rebecca.</i>

18:31.044 --> 18:33.711
<i>Leave me a message and I'll
get back to you soon as I can.</i>

18:51.331 --> 18:53.831
<i>Oh, boy,
you're hiding something, dude.</i>

18:53.833 --> 18:55.299
Mm-hmm.

18:55.301 --> 18:58.236
- Mark, come on, tell me.
- Ah, you're making me nervous.

18:58.238 --> 18:59.570
What were you gonna say?

19:02.041 --> 19:05.076
Well, I've been doing
a lot of thinking...

19:05.078 --> 19:10.882
and, um, I have realized that...

19:13.620 --> 19:16.988
nothing in this universe
matters to me...

19:16.990 --> 19:20.191
if I can't be with you
for the rest of my life.

19:21.895 --> 19:23.094
I love you, Rebecca,

19:23.096 --> 19:26.097
and I want to be
with you forever.

19:29.536 --> 19:31.035
Will you marry me?

19:32.772 --> 19:33.971
Yes.

19:34.607 --> 19:36.374
My God, yes, yes!

22:03.189 --> 22:04.322
Hmm.

22:21.207 --> 22:22.673
Honey, stop.

22:23.376 --> 22:25.042
I'm not in the mood.

22:30.149 --> 22:33.050
Jacob. Jacob, honey, wake up.

22:33.052 --> 22:34.885
- Something's touching me.
- What?

22:34.887 --> 22:36.620
Something's touching my leg.

22:38.458 --> 22:40.958
What?
Something's touching your leg?

22:44.997 --> 22:46.330
Elena.

22:46.833 --> 22:48.265
Jesus Christ.

22:48.968 --> 22:51.369
Don't move.

22:51.371 --> 22:54.672
It's a rattler, honey.
Stay perfectly still.

22:56.309 --> 22:57.341
Shh, don't move.

22:57.877 --> 22:58.976
Don't move.

22:58.978 --> 23:00.378
Stay still.

23:21.334 --> 23:25.102
- Oh, my God.
- Let me see.

23:25.104 --> 23:28.172
- Oh, God, oh, God.
- Elena, Elena. Elena!

23:28.908 --> 23:30.641
We're gonna get you
to a hospital.

23:36.282 --> 23:38.582
Breathe, Elena.
We're almost there.

23:39.619 --> 23:40.785
Jacob...

23:42.889 --> 23:44.522
I don't feel so good.

23:44.524 --> 23:46.123
I know, Elena. I know.

23:46.125 --> 23:48.192
Just hang in there.
We'd be there any minute.

23:49.095 --> 23:50.461
I love you, Jacob.

23:51.063 --> 23:52.430
I love you, Elena.

23:54.066 --> 23:55.499
Hang in there, baby.

24:01.808 --> 24:02.940
Mr. Richardson?

24:02.942 --> 24:04.809
- Yes.
- I'm Dr. Bentley.

24:04.811 --> 24:05.976
Doc, how is she?

24:05.978 --> 24:07.111
Would you come with us?

24:07.713 --> 24:08.746
Well, what?

24:12.652 --> 24:14.952
What do you mean, Doc?
Why can't I see her?

24:14.954 --> 24:18.055
Mr. Richardson,
I want you to understand

24:18.791 --> 24:20.157
we did everything we could,

24:20.159 --> 24:23.060
but your wife,
she just didn't make it.

24:24.997 --> 24:26.263
The...

24:27.033 --> 24:29.800
Because of the location
of the bite,

24:29.802 --> 24:32.570
the venom spread so fast

24:32.572 --> 24:35.706
that there was just
nothing else we could do.

24:37.343 --> 24:39.844
What you mean...
she didn't make...

24:41.214 --> 24:44.315
Because of where the bite was...

24:44.317 --> 24:46.050
Enough!

24:49.922 --> 24:52.189
Again, I'm sorry,
Mr. Richardson.

24:53.759 --> 24:55.326
I'm so sorry.

24:55.328 --> 24:57.194
I'll be right here
if you need anything.

25:22.889 --> 25:25.422
Elena, I'm so sorry.

25:27.560 --> 25:28.826
It should have been me

25:28.828 --> 25:31.328
because you didn't deserve this.

25:38.638 --> 25:42.373
You're my world,
my life.

25:43.643 --> 25:45.409
I always love you.

25:48.648 --> 25:50.147
I promise you,

25:51.551 --> 25:53.851
I will take care
of our little girl.

25:56.589 --> 25:58.923
Promise. I promise.

26:03.029 --> 26:04.728
I love you, Elena,

26:05.865 --> 26:07.698
with all my heart.

26:07.700 --> 26:11.402
I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry.

26:12.939 --> 26:16.173
Oh, God.

27:37.356 --> 27:39.590
Oh, Mark,
please forgive me.

27:57.476 --> 28:01.412
Rebecca? Rebecca?
Are you there?

28:02.081 --> 28:04.281
Mark, is that you?

28:12.458 --> 28:13.524
Mark?

28:19.498 --> 28:20.764
Mark, I'm here.

28:21.801 --> 28:24.568
Oh, my God!

28:26.305 --> 28:28.072
Mark, what's happened?

28:28.074 --> 28:29.840
Rebecca, you have
to get out of here.

28:29.842 --> 28:30.808
They're coming.

28:30.810 --> 28:32.309
- I'm not leaving.
- I don't have time to explain.

28:32.311 --> 28:33.811
- You've to go!
- No!

28:34.380 --> 28:36.680
Rebecca, go! Go!

28:42.354 --> 28:43.954
Hello, Rebecca.

28:44.890 --> 28:45.889
It's you.

28:46.325 --> 28:47.591
Why are you here?

28:47.593 --> 28:50.427
I'm here to guide you
to the other side.

28:50.429 --> 28:52.396
I'm not ready to die.

28:52.398 --> 28:54.732
It is already done, child.

28:55.468 --> 28:57.568
You can't change destiny.

28:58.104 --> 29:00.404
You must accept your fate.

29:00.840 --> 29:02.606
No! Go to hell!

29:46.118 --> 29:49.419
Mark!

29:52.658 --> 29:54.024
Help me.

29:56.262 --> 29:58.629
Rebecca, you're okay.

29:59.698 --> 30:01.932
Daddy's here. I'm here, honey.

30:04.103 --> 30:05.769
I thought I lost you.

30:05.771 --> 30:08.005
I thought I lost you, princess.

30:08.007 --> 30:10.641
Thank you, God. Thank you.

30:12.545 --> 30:14.178
Dad, I saw something.

30:15.014 --> 30:16.547
Saw what?

30:16.549 --> 30:17.981
On the other side...

30:19.351 --> 30:20.884
Mark was there.

30:21.720 --> 30:23.987
And he was suffering terribly.

30:23.989 --> 30:26.190
I saw that man, Aksel,

30:26.192 --> 30:28.492
and there was
an older man with him.

30:29.962 --> 30:31.595
I think it was his father.

30:31.597 --> 30:32.996
I think it was Henrik.

30:32.998 --> 30:36.466
What? What happened?

30:37.770 --> 30:40.037
Henrik tried to lure me to hell.

30:41.407 --> 30:43.207
He said it was my fate.

30:45.144 --> 30:47.044
And then I started burning.

30:48.247 --> 30:50.781
They're causing
all this suffering, Dad.

30:51.750 --> 30:54.618
They'll do anything they can
to destroy us.

30:55.554 --> 30:57.588
There's obviously something
on our land

30:57.590 --> 30:59.156
that they really want.

31:01.060 --> 31:03.861
Your mother tried to tell me
they were evil,

31:06.866 --> 31:09.967
thought they'd put a curse
on our family.

31:17.810 --> 31:20.878
But I wouldn't listen.

31:26.518 --> 31:28.085
I wouldn't listen, baby

31:38.030 --> 31:39.229
The girl lives.

31:40.099 --> 31:42.266
And now she knows who we are.

31:42.268 --> 31:44.534
We have failed Satan.

31:44.536 --> 31:48.272
And he will not grant us
access to his own child...

31:49.174 --> 31:50.874
if we continue to fail him.

31:50.876 --> 31:54.244
Should we take more
direct measures, Father?

31:54.246 --> 31:56.046
In time, Amund. In time.

31:56.949 --> 31:59.449
We must wait
for the right moment.

31:59.451 --> 32:01.585
Until then,
keep a close eye on them.

32:02.922 --> 32:03.954
Bring her in!

32:24.777 --> 32:29.413
Satan, we swear on our lives
that we will not fail again.

32:30.849 --> 32:34.718
Please accept this offering
as a token of our repentance.

32:41.927 --> 32:46.163
<i> Ave Satan.</i>
<i>Ave Satan.</i>

32:47.166 --> 32:51.068
<i> Ave Satan. Ave Satan.</i>

32:51.070 --> 32:53.537
- <i>Ave Satan.</i>
- <i>Ave Satan.</i>

32:53.539 --> 32:56.640
- <i>Ave Satan.</i>
